# Linux Fundamentals

Below are the Linux Networking & Protocols.

1. OSI & TCP/IP
The OSI model describes how data travels across a network in 7 layers.

7 --> Application  --> HTTP, FTP, DNS
6 --> Presentation --> SSL/TLS, encoding
5 --> Session      --> session mgmt
4 --> Transport    --> TCP, UDP
3 --> Network      --> IP, routing
2 --> Data Link    --> MAC, switches
1 --> Physical     --> cables, NICs



